singular: Returns the value of attribute singular
plural: Returns the value of attribute plural
element: Returns the value of attribute element
collection: Returns the value of attribute collection
singular_route_key: Returns the value of attribute singular_route_key
route_key: Returns the value of attribute route_key
param_key: Returns the value of attribute param_key
i18n_key: Returns the value of attribute i18n_key
name: Returns the value of attribute name
cache_key: Returns the value of attribute collection
initialize:
Returns a new ActiveModel::Name instance. By default, the +namespace+
and +name+ option will take the namespace and name of the given class
respectively.

  module Foo
    class Bar
    end
  end

  ActiveModel::Name.new(Foo::Bar).to_s
  # => "Foo::Bar"
human:
Transform the model name into a more humane format, using I18n. By default,
it will underscore then humanize the class name.

  class BlogPost
    extend ActiveModel::Naming
  end

  BlogPost.model_name.human # => "Blog post"

Specify +options+ with additional translating options.
